parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck in the open throttle position
the vehicle surges forward when accelerated
the brakes are unable to stop the acceleration
the wrench warning indicator illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The transmission fails while driving
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle is unable to maintain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter mechanism can cause the vehicle to roll backwards or lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The shifter does not stay in place
the vehicle does not stay in gear
the vehicle rolls backwards
the pin in the shifter is not working.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System or Catalytic Converter Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system or catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to emit strong, unpleasant odors, which can be a sign of a more serious underlying problem.
symptoms: The vehicle emits a strong
sulfur-like (egg-like) smell
the smell is more noticeable after long trips or hot days
the smell has been persistent for several years.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the vehicle to lurch or stall, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially when stopping or slowing down.
symptoms: The vehicle lurches or jerks when coming to a stop
the vehicle idles roughly or makes an airy sound
the vehicle's brakes wear out prematurely
the vehicle's powertrain warning lights illuminate
the vehicle spins out of control or stalls.
